@node "introduction" ".-^ INTRODUCTION ^-."
@next "install"
@prev "main"
@{b}@{u} Immunity Introduction @{ub}@{uu}

Immunity is a DOS-BBS-TOOL for all BBS Systems that support filechecking by
normal dos programs.
If your BBS System doesn't support this "feature" change the BBSSystem ;)
Immunity isn't a self-contained VirusChecker, it needs VirusWorkShop 
Đ by Flake/TRSi.
BTW special thank's to him for his great VirusChecker. 
Without VirusWorkShop Immunity wouldn't exist.

I began to code this BBS-Tool when i recognized that my System was again 
infected by viruses due to my BBS.
So i start to make a program that can communicate with VirusWorkShop and can
be used from the archivechecking-script of my board.
Now you've got the result on your System :
- Runs on nearly all BBSSystems
- Works together with VirusWorkShop by Flake/TRSi
- Cool Style
- Fast Checking
- Can create a lofile when a virus has been detected by VW
- E-Mail Ware
- Supports LHA/LZH/LZX


@{b}@{u} Requirements: @{ub}@{uu}
 
  - An Amiga ;)
  - A Bulletin Board System that supports filechecking by dos programs
  - VirusWorkShop (6.4) by Flake/TRSi
 
                            @{" BACK 2 MAINMENU " link "main" 0}
@endnode

@node "install" ".-^ INSTALLATION ^-."
@next "config"
@prev "introduction"
@{b}@{u} Installation: @{ub}@{uu}

Copy the directory "Immunity" where ya want and make an assign called
"IMMUNITY" to it. Without this assign it won't work.
Now install it to the filechecking part of your bbssystem.
If ya don't know how to install an archivechecker then read your 
bbsdocs ;)
Immunity supports following archivetypes :
- LHA
- LZH
- LZX

Immunity only needs the name and the filepath of the uploaded file, so
you must call it like this :

@{b}@{FG SHINE}IMMUNITY:IMMUNITY <path:filename>@{PARD}

If you're finished with this part you have to edit the ConfigFile
called "IMMUNITY.CFG" :
In the @{FG SHINE}first line@{PARD} you are asked if Immunity should 
create/append a log file, if a virus was found inside a archive.
Fill in @{FG SHINE}YES@{PARD} or @{FG SHINE}NO@{PARD}.
In the @{FG SHINE}second line@{PARD} you are asked for the @{FG SHINE}desired path and name of the
logfile@{PARD}.
If the 1st line says NO you don't need to fill out this line.
It could look like this :
@{b}@{FG SHINE}

YES
IMMUNITY:LOGF.TXT
------------------------------------------------------------------------
1st line : Create LogFile if a Virus is detected inside a archive YES/NO
2nd line : Desired path and name of the LogFile
@{PARD}
@{b}
- You have to start VirusWorkShop allways, before you use Immunity!
- Turn on VirusWorkShop's Automaticmode
- Don't forget to create a directory for VirusWorkShop where the
  archives will be extracted and checked.
- Don't forget to make an assign called 'VWLHA' to this directory.
- VirusWorkShop will delete all detected Viruses.
@{PARD}

SO...THAT'S ALL...HAVE FUN WITH YOUR IMMUNE BOARD ;)

                            @{" BACK 2 MAINMENU " link "main" 0}

@endnode

